{"name":"Broadcast the team on new events with Outlook end to end","nodes":[{"parameters":{"httpMethod":"POST","path":"wf09071-order","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.webhook","typeVersion":2,"position":[-270,400],"id":"7a1bb5f8-ca89-4818-99c7-16f12ad52e63","name":"Receive Inbound Webhook","webhookId":"e2bd6f25-9fe1-4253-95ac-b65ef4905de5"},{"parameters":{"method":"GET","url":"https://api.example.com/v1/orders","options":{"timeout":20000},"sendQuery":true,"queryParameters":{"parameters":[{"name":"updated_since","value":"={{ $now.minus({hours: 6}).toISO() }}"},{"name":"limit","value":"100"}]}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest","typeVersion":4.2,"position":[54,400],"id":"e8fe3556-72ba-43f0-93b3-4ced66186751","name":"Fetch Current Metrics","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"mode":"runOnceForAllItems","jsCode":"// Score each order 0-100 from simple heuristics\nreturn $input.all().map(item => {\n  const j = item.json;\n  let score = 50;\n  if (j.email) score += 20;\n  if (j.total) score += 15;\n  if ((j.source || '') === 'referral') score += 15;\n  return { json: { ...j, score: Math.min(100, score) } };\n});"},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.code","typeVersion":2,"position":[378,400],"id":"15624800-6a4b-4df4-b4e4-ad8c887caf1d","name":"Compute Severity Signals"},{"parameters":{"rules":{"values":[{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"773c7ac6-44f5-4a43-9ba8-8cbd921df080","leftValue":"={{ $json.score ?? $json.momentum ?? 0 }}","rightValue":40,"operator":{"type":"number","operation":"lt"}}],"combinator":"and"},"renameOutput":true,"outputKey":"info"},{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"4178cd67-83b1-4aea-aa03-40c1ee6c4276","leftValue":"={{ $json.score ?? $json.momentum ?? 0 }}","rightValue":70,"operator":{"type":"number","operation":"gte"}}],"combinator":"and"},"renameOutput":true,"outputKey":"warning"},{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"37a0b610-e0fc-485c-8677-957ef6425499","leftValue":"={{ $json.score ?? $json.momentum ?? 0 }}","rightValue":90,"operator":{"type":"number","operation":"gte"}}],"combinator":"and"},"renameOutput":true,"outputKey":"critical"}]},"options":{"fallbackOutput":"extra"}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.switch","typeVersion":3.2,"position":[702,400],"id":"7f52e4c7-a606-4ce9-a03a-2a0a660b38f4","name":"Grade Severity Tier"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Order Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[1026,-80],"id":"fd2825da-c1c1-4ac9-affb-b915fd12956c","name":"Just Record (Info)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"subject":"=🟠 Warning tier reached: {{ $json.orderId }} at {{ $json.score ?? $json.last }}","bodyContent":"=🟠 Warning tier reached: {{ $json.orderId }} at {{ $json.score ?? $json.last }}","toRecipients":"={{ $json.email || 'ops@company.com' }}","additionalFields":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.microsoftOutlook","typeVersion":2,"position":[1350,400],"id":"a5f6d229-5fa9-41b3-a8e8-94d6288f8ea6","name":"Warn Channel (Outlook)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#orders","cachedResultName":"#orders"},"text":"=🔴 CRITICAL: {{ $json.orderId }} breached threshold — act now","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[1674,880],"id":"5ad6c6f8-74df-466e-95cf-142b67a71e43","name":"Page Urgently (Slack)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Order Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[1998,1360],"id":"272ddf32-99ee-4caa-8e96-d24b93d4efd2","name":"Archive Unscored","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"mode":"append","numberInputs":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.merge","typeVersion":3.2,"position":[2646,400],"id":"e86d8c2f-45fa-482f-b74f-c6805ab40f7e","name":"Merge Tier Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"method":"GET","url":"https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup","sendQuery":true,"queryParameters":{"parameters":[{"name":"query","value":"={{ $json.email }}"}]},"options":{"timeout":15000}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest","typeVersion":4.2,"position":[3618,400],"id":"b3886101-39ca-4690-b308-7189cb175f0a","name":"Enrich with Reference Data","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"alwaysOutputData":true,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"be1de3e0-25c0-4aa0-8dff-2f10dab927f0","name":"enrichedAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"b5f6768e-3b55-4827-89d9-d3f0fe8fdaea","name":"enrichmentSource","value":"reference-api","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[3942,400],"id":"56608c36-b51f-48ff-9d07-338662a00ab9","name":"Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"operation":"csv","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.convertToFile","typeVersion":1.1,"position":[4266,400],"id":"60b14b16-5ac0-416f-8377-29ec2e437cf3","name":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Order Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[4590,400],"id":"2cb30ca3-828e-43b9-9288-978a9cf8efb6","name":"Archive Row Snapshot","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"operation":"getCurrentDate","outputFieldName":"completedAt","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.dateTime","typeVersion":2,"position":[4914,400],"id":"df34de20-622b-488f-8176-bf123103c07e","name":"Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"dataToSave":{"values":[{"key":"runId","value":"={{ $execution.id }}"},{"key":"itemCount","value":"={{ $items().length }}"}]}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.executionData","typeVersion":1,"position":[5238,400],"id":"58a5e8a8-2c6a-4c73-86b7-983ce2128205","name":"Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"40abd6b3-0b2f-4f66-a470-ef2ef14f1515","name":"runAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"f60e9e7c-5f69-413f-9a66-650624ab9b2f","name":"itemCount","value":"={{ $input.all().length }}","type":"number"},{"id":"00c6199c-d35b-4106-bdc4-d985fdb8a367","name":"status","value":"completed","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5562,400],"id":"54c8aa66-3c1d-4982-965a-cc4402623022","name":"Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Order Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[5886,400],"id":"8a7131ce-6826-46a9-aaed-3f9d364f2c35","name":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"subject":"=✅ Broadcast the team on new events with Outlook end to end — run completed at {","bodyContent":"=✅ Broadcast the team on new events with Outlook end to end — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","toRecipients":"={{ $json.email || 'ops@company.com' }}","additionalFields":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.microsoftOutlook","typeVersion":2,"position":[6210,400],"id":"9e524cf2-9b54-4991-900f-2a3dc6534316","name":"Send Summary to Outlook","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"b4182f34-b060-4048-97cb-9cfc6ee2f978","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"bb51baf2-bd90-44d1-9c4e-79d2246182ed","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"bf9bad23-2b25-4e07-9150-d5c09ece5bcd","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5562,1420],"id":"048d7364-c6a8-47d8-9d2c-9a9c926f75f5","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#orders","cachedResultName":"#orders"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5886,1420],"id":"6343eba8-32e1-470a-8422-bd538b57ead7","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Order Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[6210,1420],"id":"42067374-b7c9-4d34-acbc-5d32a21d873d","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf09071-order`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Fetch Current Metrics","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"39d70fb4-f343-8288-ffed-23db2946b914","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fetch Current Metrics\n\nGET https://api.example.com/v1/orders — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Severity Signals · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"244c2314-85cb-7cfc-87c7-e93fb510e7e6","name":"Note: Fetch Current Metrics"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Severity Signals\n\nCustom JavaScript: Score each order 0-100 from simple heuristics\n\nNext: Grade Severity Tier","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"eadc4dce-3f10-1a09-f25a-7eb5894d7e2d","name":"Note: Compute Severity Signals"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Grade Severity Tier\n\nRoutes each item to one of 4 lanes: info, warning, critical + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Just Record (Info) · ②→ Warn Channel (Outlook) · ③→ Page Urgently (Slack) · ④→ Archive Unscored","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"c136743f-ceff-51fd-4759-ebae98e40f9b","name":"Note: Grade Severity Tier"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Just Record (Info)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Order Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,40],"id":"6802b73c-349d-8ff6-3775-3551529b9c19","name":"Note: Just Record (Info)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Warn Channel (Outlook)\n\nSends an email via Microsoft Outlook — recipient comes from the item's `email` field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"2e07c511-18bd-03c5-ede2-a60923c0c921","name":"Note: Warn Channel (Outlook)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Page Urgently (Slack)\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#orders`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,1000],"id":"45db60c5-94ec-6827-56a8-f8f790a60cc9","name":"Note: Page Urgently (Slack)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Unscored\n\nAppends a new row to 'Order Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Tier Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,1480],"id":"d98572e4-2e22-d487-147c-8eb6be9f93f2","name":"Note: Archive Unscored"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Tier Outcomes\n\nRejoins 4 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,520],"id":"b20087cf-4480-496b-de03-ab06a8ffd9df","name":"Note: Merge Tier Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"288c75da-7e58-0170-8ba7-6edd185261d7","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"33f9ac51-2997-1259-2bd7-1b254d27a1cf","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"68e68551-ea3d-c13f-5cee-dfc780603208","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nAppends a new row to 'Order Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Stamp Completion Time · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"83156f9b-fde7-7ec4-c958-d835eece5f0f","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"08b9bd9c-c2cd-3578-ca35-6e98146b7631","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"8e781ca6-2455-805d-36ed-66e52ce3cfd0","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"232a61f7-fcc2-8892-bd00-9d8ba0eae5ef","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Order Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Outlook · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"bf1a0fa8-fc5c-7cf2-b0db-e7d92d3cb328","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Outlook\n\nSends an email via Microsoft Outlook — recipient comes from the item's `email` field.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"7c0214ef-d1c7-d96d-7f19-6901da7a85fe","name":"Note: Send Summary to Outlook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,1540],"id":"40282dcd-b056-cf22-f3a3-b33d579428c2","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#orders`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,1540],"id":"05bb4549-9285-c947-a0a1-59e6c6e3fda0","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nAppends a new row to 'Order Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,1540],"id":"da2e6b23-464a-f92f-1c71-32ed16cd6e9b","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Broadcast the team on new events with Outlook end to end\n\n**Pattern:** Event Notification · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nBroadcast the team on new events with Outlook end to end. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual cart recovery is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Fetch Current Metrics → Compute Severity Signals → Grade Severity Tier → Just Record (Info) → Merge Tier Outcomes → Enrich with Reference Data → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to event notification without manual effort\n- Anyone automating cart recovery in e-commerce\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Responds in seconds\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"afd0df3d-625d-69e2-967e-86b52ea3fb43","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nThree response tiers, not a single yes/no alert, match the response to the severity — logging every metric quietly would bury the one critical spike, and paging on-call for every info-level blip trains them to ignore alerts entirely. Critical gets a distinct, louder channel from warning on purpose.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"9a9d03a5-c2ad-9a9c-ff90-a35015dd2db8","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAlready production-grade — deepen your understanding:\n\n1. Adjust the tier thresholds and see how alert sensitivity changes.\n2. Trigger a critical-tier value and confirm it pages a different channel than warning does.\n3. Add a 4th tier between warning and critical.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"13f0e195-d30b-153b-5066-0b56842283e7","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"5ebbc1cf-6f50-8891-5790-c9f5b729f72f","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"c2f3d1d1-e84f-e377-eb83-3576f01f62fe","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your cart recovery process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"7ddd063c-787f-20ce-e4d9-b22cbe038ae6","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Fetch Current Metrics","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fetch Current Metrics":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Severity Signals","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Severity Signals":{"main":[[{"node":"Grade Severity Tier","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Grade Severity Tier":{"main":[[{"node":"Just Record (Info)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Warn Channel (Outlook)","type":"main"